Problem Statement

You are given an array A of size N.
You can partition A into multiple contiguous subarrays such that each element belongs to exactly one subarray and each subarray has a length of at least K.
The "beauty" of a subarray is the maximum bitwise XOR of the values of ANY subset in that subarray. 
The "amazingness" of a partitioned array is the sum of beauties of its subarrays.

Find the maximum possible amazingness of A.

Constraints
1 <= N <= 10^5
1 <= K <= 10^5
1 <= A[i] <= 10^5

